    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-07-03T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-07-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="1577"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1577">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 819.00/419.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">American Minister</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-07-03">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 3, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Members of the Unión Patriótica have sent the President a telegram translated as
                    follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>The undersigned directors and members of the Patriotic Union, assembled
                            in a special meeting, hereby respectfully present to you our formal
                            protest against the fraudulent and scandalous manner in which the recent
                            elections were carried out, and we earnestly entreat you to have the
                            next ones postponed long enough for us to present proofs to yon of the
                            frauds and partialities committed in the elections held yesterday, so
                            that we may request their annulment and that means may be adopted for
                            the holding of a new election which shall record the real opinion of the
                            people.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>To which answer is being made on behalf of the President: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>Complaint contained in your telegram, which has been referred to this
                            Department for a reply, would seem to be a matter which might properly
                            be laid before the supervision committee for its recommendation.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Knox.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
